4 a) Write a program to apply different types of selector forms 

i. Simple selector (element, id, class, group, universal)

ii. Combinator selector (descendant, child, adjacent sibling, general sibling)

iii. Pseudo-class selector

iv. Pseudo-element selector

v. Attribute selector

Aim: To create a webpage that demonstrates the use of different types of CSS selectors for styling HTML 

elements.

Description:

Selector Type Example Description

Element h1 Selects all <h1>

ID #main-title Selects element with that ID

Class .highlight Selects elements with that class

Group h2, p, li Applies same rule to multiple elements

Universal * Applies to all elements

Combinator Example Matches...

Descendant div p All <p> inside <div>

Child ul > li Direct children only

Adjacent h3 + p First <p> immediately after <h3>

General h3 ~ p All <p> after <h3> siblings

Pseudo-class Example

:hover Link effects

:first-child, :nth-child(n) Position-based selection

Pseudo-element Example

::first-line Style first line of text

::before, ::after Inject content before/after element

Program:

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

 <meta charset="UTF-8">

 <title>CSS Selector Types Demo</title>

 <style>

 /* I. Simple Selectors */

 h1 { color: darkblue; } /* Element selector */

 #main-title { text-decoration: underline; }/* ID selector */

 .highlight { background-color: yellow; } /* Class selector */

 h2, p, li { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; } /* Group selector */

 * { margin: 5px; } /* Universal selector */

 /* II. Combinator Selectors */

 div p { color: green; } /* Descendant selector */

 ul > li { font-weight: bold; } /* Child selector */

 h3 + p { color: red; } /* Adjacent sibling */

 h3 ~ p { font-style: italic; } /* General sibling */

 /* III. Pseudo-class Selectors */

 a:hover { color: orange; } /* Hover effect */

 li:first-child { color: purple; } /* First child */

 li:nth-child(2) { color: teal; } /* Specific child */

 /* IV. Pseudo-element Selectors */

 p::first-line { font-weight: bold; } /* First line of a paragraph */

 p::before { content: " "; color: gray; } /* Before content */
p::after { content: " "; color: green; } /* After content */

 /* V. Attribute Selectors */

 input[type="text"] { border: 2px solid blue; }

 a[href^="https"] { font-style: italic; }

 input[placeholder*="name"] { background-color: #f0f8ff; }

 </style>

</head>

<body>

 <!-- Simple Selectors -->

 <h1 id="main-title">CSS Selector Examples</h1>

 <h2 class="highlight">This is a highlighted heading</h2>

 <!-- Combinator Selectors -->

 <div>

 <p>This paragraph is a descendant of a div.</p>

 </div>

 <ul>

 <li>First Item</li>

 <li>Second Item</li>

 <li>Third Item</li>

 </ul>

 <h3>Heading for siblings</h3>

 <p>This paragraph is adjacent sibling of h3.</p>

 <p>This paragraph is a general sibling of h3.</p>

 <!-- Pseudo-class -->

 <a href="https://www.example.com">Visit Example</a>

 <!-- Pseudo-element -->

 <p>This paragraph demonstrates pseudo-elements.</p>

 <!-- Attribute Selectors -->

 <form>

 <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your name">

 <input type="email" placeholder="Enter your email">

 </form>

</body>

</html>

Output:


